The Nigerian National Petroleum Company (NNPC) has released names of filling stations operating for 24 hours in Abuja and its environs to curb the supply deficiencies in the country. The oil firm disclosed this on its official Twitter page on Monday. Over the past few weeks, Nigerians have been battling petrol scarcity, after the supply chain was disrupted due to the importation of methanol-blended petrol. TheCable had reported how the off-spec petrol saga maimed economic activities in the country. Responding to the development, the NNPC had said it would begin 24-hour operations at its depots and fuel stations to bridge the gap in the supply chain. SEE FULL LIST: FILLING STATIONS OPERATING FOR 24 HOURS IN ABUJA 